"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:9.1.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">9.1.1</span> New wine</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">עָסִיס</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(‘asis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:2\">SNG 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:26\">ISA 49:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:5\">JOL 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel4:18\">JOL 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:13\">AMO 9:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">תִּירוֹשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tirosh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:28\">GEN 27:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:37\">GEN 27:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:12\">NUM 18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13\">DEU 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:14\">DEU 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:17\">DEU 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:23\">DEU 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:4\">DEU 18:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:51\">DEU 28:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:28\">DEU 33:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:13\">JDG 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:32\">2KI 18:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:5\">2CH 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:28\">2CH 32:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:11\">NEH 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:38\">NEH 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:40\">NEH 10:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:5\">NEH 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:12\">NEH 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:8\">PSA 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:10\">PRO 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:7\">ISA 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:17\">ISA 36:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:8\">ISA 62:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:8\">ISA 65:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:12\">JER 31:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:10\">HOS 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:11\">HOS 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:24\">HOS 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:11\">HOS 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:14\">HOS 7:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:2\">HOS 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:10\">JOL 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:19\">JOL 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:24\">JOL 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:15\">MIC 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:11\">HAG 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:17\">ZEC 9:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">οἶνος, νέος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(oinos neos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:38\">LUK 5:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir9:10\">SIR 9:10</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>New wine was newly pressed grape juice, unfermented or in the initial stages of fermentation.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>While the Hebrew words <em>‘asis</em> and <em>tirosh</em> may refer to unfermented juice, they sometimes indicate wine in the first stages of fermentation. Some languages, especially in wine-growing areas, have a special word for this drink, which is available for only a short time after the grape harvest. The context may indicate if the beverage intended is fermented or not. Where it is determined that fermented juice is spoken of, translators may simply render <em>‘asis</em> or <em>tirosh</em> as “wine,” which <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> does in the middle of <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:13\">JDG 9:13</a>: “I would have to stop producing my wine.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
